        "subtopic": "Basic Formulas",
        "content": "**Simple Interest (SI) = (P × R × T) / 100**\nWhere:\nP = Principal (initial amount)\nR = Rate of Interest per annum\nT = Time in years\n\n**Total Amount (A) = Principal + SI = P + (P × R × T)/100**"
      }
