      {
        "subtopic": "Finding Principal",
        "content": "**Q:** If the SI earned in 2 years at 10% p.a. is ₹300, find the principal.\n\n**Solution:**\nSI = (P × R × T)/100\n300 = (P × 10 × 2)/100 ⇒ 300 = P × 0.2 ⇒ P = ₹1500\n\n**Answer:** ₹1500"
